icActionsMobile\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_main_2530156\" data-toggle=\"modal\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-feedback\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-feedback\"></use></svg><span class=\"zDocsFeedbackButtonText\"> Feedback</span></span></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><button aria-label=\"Show topic actions\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" id=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-ellipsis-h\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-ellipsis-h\"></use></svg></button><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu zDocsTopicActionsMobileDropdown dropdown-menu-right\"></div></div><div style=\"flex-basis: 100%; height: 0px;\"></div><ul class=\"zDocsTopicPageDetails\"><li class=\"zDocsTopicPageDate css-cinqea\">Last Updated<span class=\"css-cinqea\">Aug 05, 2024</span></li><li class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryDetailsItem\"><button class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryButton\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-topic-summary\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-topic-summary\"></use></svg>Summarize</button></li><li class=\"spacer\" role=\"presentation\"></li><div class=\"zDocsLabelWrapper\"><ul><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: Uniface\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=prod_uniface\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>Uniface</a></li><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: 10.4\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=uniface_10.4\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>10.4</a></li></ul></div></ul></header><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBody\" data-prismjs-copy=\"Copy\" data-prismjs-copy-error=\"Copy failed! Use Ctrl + C instead.\" data-prismjs-copy-success=\"Copied!\"><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBodyContent wide\" dir=\"ltr\"><div id=\"zDocsAiSummaryContaineruniface_104mzr1665702983304.html\"></div><div><article class=\"hascomments\" data-page=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/mzr1665702983304.html\" id=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/mzr1665702983304.html\"><main role=\"main\"><article aria-labelledby=\"ariaid-title1\" class=\"dita\" id=\"mzr1665702983304\" role=\"article\">\n<h1 class=\"title topictitle1\" id=\"ariaid-title1\">\n      Parameters in the Output Sequence\n </h1>\n<div class=\"body conbody\"><p class=\"shortdesc\">Some mnemonics include parameters in the output sequence that can be used to determine layout and formatting information, such as horizontal and vertical coordinates, numeric base zero (decimal, octal, or hexadecimal), zero padding, and so on. The output sequence can even include expressions that use the parameters incalculation, for example, to increment values.\n </p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"mzr1665702983304__p_d63794e1_d63795e1_d63796e1\">In many cases, Uniface adapts the way it operates based on which parameters are included. The exact parameters passed and how Uniface reacts are described with each mnemonic.</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"mzr1665702983304__p_d63797e1_d63798e1_d63799e1\">For example, if the <code class=\"ph codeph\">%p</code> parameter is not included in the output sequence for the buzz mnemonic, Uniface assumes that the device cannot buzz several times with one command; the buzz command is then activated p times.</p>\n<div class=\"table-wrap\"><table class=\"table\" count-columns=\"2\" id=\"mzr1665702983304__table_d5564e1_d5565e1_d5566e1\"><caption><span class=\"table--title-label\">Table 1. </span><span class=\"title\">Parameters in the output sequence</span></caption><colgroup><col/><col/></colgroup><thead class=\"thead\">\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<th class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" id=\"mzr1665702983304__table_d5564e1_d5565e1_d5566e1__entry__1\">\n Parameters\n </th>\n<th class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" id=\"mzr1665702983304__table_d5564e1_d5565e1_d5566e1__entry__2\">\n Meaning\n </th>\n</tr>\n</thead><tbody class=\"tbody\">\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"mzr1665702983304__table_d5564e1_d5565e1_d5566e1__entry__1\">\n %h %v\n </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"mzr1665702983304__table_d5564e1_d5565e1_d5566e1__entry__2\">\n Horizontal and vertical starting coordinates.\n </td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"mzr1665702983304__table_d5564e1_d5565e1_d5566e1__entry__1\">\n %m\n </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"mzr1665702983304__table_d5564e1_d5565e1_d5566e1__entry__2\">\n Repetition (<var class=\"keyword varname\">m</var> times) of character. Useful for white space.\n </td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"mzr1665702983304__table_d5564e1_d5565e1_d5566e1__entry__1\">\n %m %n\n </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"mzr1665702983304__table_d5564e1_d5565e1_d5566e1__entry__2\">\n Horizontal width and vertical depth.\n </td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"mzr1665702983304__table_d5564e1_d5565e1_d5566e1__entry__1\">\n %x %y\n </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"mzr1665702983304__table_d5564e1_d5565e1_d5566e1__entry__2\">\n Horizontal and vertical ending coordinates.\n </td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"mzr1665702983304__table_d5564e1_d5565e1_d5566e1__entry__1\">\n %p %q\n </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"mzr1665702983304__table_d5564e1_d5565e1_d5566e1__entry__2\">\n General parameters, often used as a kind of counter.\n </td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"mzr1665702983304__table_d5564e1_d5565e1_d5566e1__entry__1\">\n %w %d\n </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"mzr1665702983304__table_d5564e1_d5565e1_d5566e1__entry__2\">\n Character width and depth, that is, resolution.\n </td>\n</tr>\n</tbody></table></div>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"mzr1665702983304__section_o2x_nvh_hcc\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d1074013e146\">Formatting the Output Sequence</h2>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"mzr1665702983304__p_d63803e1_d63804e1_d63805e1\">All of these parameters can be preceded by a number\n            which determines how Uniface formats the data, that is, which base (decimal, octal, or\n            hexadecimal), and whether the number should be padded with zeros to a fixed length. The\n            syntax is shown in the table, where a question mark (?) is a single digit 1 through\n            9:</p>\n<div class=\"table-wrap\"><table class=\"table\" count-columns=\"2\" id=\"mzr1665702983304__table_d5567e1_d5568e1_d5569e1\"><caption><span class=\"table--title-label\">Table 2. </span><span class=\"title\">Data Formatting Syntax</span></caption><colgroup><col/><col/></colgroup><thead class=\"thead\">\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<th class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" id=\"mzr1665702983304__table_d5567e1_d5568e1_d5569e1__entry__1\">Parameters </th>\n<th class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" id=\"mzr1665702983304__table_d5567e1_d5568e1_d5569e1__entry__2\">Meaning </th>\n</tr>\n</thead><tbody class=\"tbody\">\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"mzr1665702983304__table_d5567e1_d5568e1_d5569e1__entry__1\">%0p or %p </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"mzr1665702983304__table_d5567e1_d5568e1_d5569e1__entry__2\">Decimal value with variable number of digits\n                        (that is, no padding). </td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"mzr1665702983304__table_d5567e1_d5568e1_d5569e1__entry__1\">%?p </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"mzr1665702983304__table_d5567e1_d5568e1_d5569e1__entry__2\">Decimal value padded with leading zeros to ?\n                        digits. </td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"mzr1665702983304__table_d5567e1_d5568e1_d5569e1__entry__1\">%10p </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"mzr1665702983304__table_d5567e1_d5568e1_d5569e1__entry__2\">Octal value with variable number of digits.\n                     </td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"mzr1665702983304__table_d5567e1_d5568e1_d5569e1__entry__1\">%1?p </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"mzr1665702983304__table_d5567e1_d5568e1_d5569e1__entry__2\">Octal value padded with leading zeros to ?\n                        digits. </td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"mzr1665702983304__table_d5567e1_d5568e1_d5569e1__entry__1\">%20p </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"mzr1665702983304__table_d5567e1_d5568e1_d5569e1__entry__2\">Hexadecimal value with variable number of\n                        digits. </td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"mzr1665702983304__table_d5567e1_d5568e1_d5569e1__entry__1\">%2?p </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"mzr1665702983304__table_d5567e1_d5568e1_d5569e1__entry__2\">Hexadecimal value padded with leading zeros to\n                        ? digits. </td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"mzr1665702983304__table_d5567e1_d5568e1_d5569e1__entry__1\">%30p </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"mzr1665702983304__table_d5567e1_d5568e1_d5569e1__entry__2\">Binary value, bytes ordered low to high,\n                        variable number of bytes. </td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"mzr1665702983304__table_d5567e1_d5568e1_d5569e1__entry__1\">%3?p </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"mzr1665702983304__table_d5567e1_d5568e1_d5569e1__entry__2\">Binary value, bytes ordered low to high.\n                     </td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"mzr1665702983304__table_d5567e1_d5568e1_d5569e1__entry__1\">%40p </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"mzr1665702983304__table_d5567e1_d5568e1_d5569e1__entry__2\">Binary value, bytes ordered high to low,\n                        variable number of bytes. </td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"mzr1665702983304__table_d5567e1_d5568e1_d5569e1__entry__1\">%4?p </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"mzr1665702983304__table_d5567e1_d5568e1_d5569e1__entry__2\">Binary value, bytes ordered high to low.\n                     </td>\n</tr>\n</tbody></table></div>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"mzr1665702983304__p_d63806e1_d63807e1_d63808e1\">For example, if Uniface needs to pass the value 17 as\n            a parameter, the table shows the literal values that are generated with the\n            corresponding codes:</p>\n<div class=\"table-wrap\"><table class=\"table\" count-columns=\"3\" id=\"mzr1665702983304__table_d5570e1_d5571e1_d5572e1\"><caption><span class=\"table--title-label\">Table 3. </span><span class=\"title\">Examples: Data Formatting Parameters</span></caption><colgroup><col/><col/><col/></colgroup><thead class=\"thead\">\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<th class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" id=\"mzr1665702983304__table_d5570e1_d5571e1_d5572e1__entry__1\">Parameter </th>\n<th class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" id=\"mzr1665702983304__table_d5570e1_d5571e1_d5572e1__entry__2\">Meaning </th>\n<th class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" id=\"mzr1665702983304__table_d5570e1_d5571e1_d5572e1__entry__3\">Value generated </th>\n</tr>\n</thead><tbody class=\"tbody\">\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"mzr1665702983304__table_d5570e1_d5571e1_d5572e1__entry__1\">%0p </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"mzr1665702983304__table_d5570e1_d5571e1_d5572e1__entry__2\">Decimal. </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"mzr1665702983304__table_d5570e1_d5571e1_d5572e1__entry__3\">17 </td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"mzr1665702983304__table_d5570e1_d5571e1_d5572e1__entry__1\">%3p </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"mzr1665702983304__table_d5570e1_d5571e1_d5572e1__entry__2\">Decimal, padded to three digits. </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"mzr1665702983304__table_d5570e1_d5571e1_d5572e1__entry__3\">017 </td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"mzr1665702983304__table_d5570e1_d5571e1_d5572e1__entry__1\">%14p </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"mzr1665702983304__table_d5570e1_d5571e1_d5572e1__entry__2\">Octal, padded to four digits. </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"mzr1665702983304__table_d5570e1_d5571e1_d5572e1__entry__3\">0021 </td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"mzr1665702983304__table_d5570e1_d5571e1_d5572e1__entry__1\">%20p </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"mzr1665702983304__table_d5570e1_d5571e1_d5572e1__entry__2\">Hexadecimal. </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"mzr1665702983304__table_d5570e1_d5571e1_d5572e1__entry__3\">11 </td>\n</tr>\n</tbody></table></div>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"mzr1665702983304__section_mj5_qvh_hcc\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d1074013e358\">Expressions in an Output Sequence</h2>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"mzr1665702983304__p_d63812e1_d63813e1_d63814e1\">Uniface also supports expressions within an output\n            sequence. An expression must be enclosed in parentheses. The indicator for base and\n            padding of the final result goes between the percent sign (%) and the opening bracket\n            (() of the expression. Values within the expression are always decimal; formatting\n            occurs at the last step. All operators supported by the ProcScript language are\n            available here, including brackets (()).</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"mzr1665702983304__p_d63815e1_d63816e1_d63817e1\">The expressions can use integer constants and all\n            parameters appropriate for the particular mnemonic. Parameters within the expression are\n            not preceded by a percent sign (%). Spaces are allowed within the expressions to\n            increase readability. If a part of the expression contains a comparison operator (for\n            example, =, &lt;, &gt;, and so on) that section expression is evaluated as a Boolean\n            expression. For example, %(2+2&lt;(2+1)) is evaluated as 3.</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"mzr1665702983304__p_d63818e1_d63819e1_d63820e1\">A few examples are given in the table:</p>\n<div class=\"table-wrap\"><table class=\"table\" count-columns=\"2\" id=\"mzr1665702983304__table_d5573e1_d5574e1_d5575e1\"><caption><span class=\"table--title-label\">Table 4. </span><span class=\"title\">Examples: Expressions in Parameter Declarations</span></caption><colgroup><col/><col/></colgroup><thead class=\"thead\">\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<th class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" id=\"mzr1665702983304__table_d5573e1_d5574e1_d5575e1__entry__1\">Parameters </th>\n<th class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" id=\"mzr1665702983304__table_d5573e1_d5574e1_d5575e1__entry__2\">Meaning </th>\n</tr>\n</thead><tbody class=\"tbody\">\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"mzr1665702983304__table_d5573e1_d5574e1_d5575e1__entry__1\">%(p+1) </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"mzr1665702983304__table_d5573e1_d5574e1_d5575e1__entry__2\">Increase ‘p’ by one. </td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"mzr1665702983304__table_d5573e1_d5574e1_d5575e1__entry__1\">%24(8 * (y + w * 16)) </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"mzr1665702983304__table_d5573e1_d5574e1_d5575e1__entry__2\">Use ‘y’ and ‘w’ in a calculation. </td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"mzr1665702983304__table_d5573e1_d5574e1_d5575e1__entry__1\">%(p%8) </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"mzr1665702983304__table_d5573e1_d5574e1_d5575e1__entry__2\">Use modulus to compute a value between 0 and 7,\n                        inclusive. </td>\n</tr>\n</tbody></table></div>\n</section>\n</div>\n</article></main></article>\n</div></div></div><div class=\"bottomFeedback\"><div aria-labelledby=\"bottomFeedbackText\" class=\"bottomFeedbackContent\" role=\"group\"><span class=\"bottomFeedbackText\" id=\"bottomFeedbackText\">Was this topic helpful?</span><div class=\"bottomFeedbackButtonGroup\"><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2530156\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-up\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-up\"></use></svg><span>Like</span></a><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2530156\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-down\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-down\"></use></svg><span>Dislike</span></a></div></div></div><div style=\"position: fixed; bottom: 170px; right: 70px; cursor: pointer; transition-duration: 0.2s; transition-timing-function: linear; transition-delay: 0s; z-index: 3; opacity: 0; visibility: hidden; transition-property: opacity, visibility;\"><button aria-label=\"Scroll to top\" class=\"zDocsScrollTopBtn\" data-tooltip-content=\"Scroll to top\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsBackToTopToolTip\" id=\"zDocsScrollToTop\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-next\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-next\"></use></svg></button></div></body></html>", "text": "Parameters in the Output Sequence Add to My Topics Add selected topic and subtopics Add Topic & Subtopics with topic head Add entire publication Watch Download PDF Save selected topic Save selected topic and subtopics Save entire publication Share Email Link Copy Link Feedback Last Updated Aug 05, 2024 Summarize Uniface 10.4 Parameters in the Output Sequence Some mnemonics include parameters in the output sequence that can be used to determine layout and formatting information, such as horizontal and vertical coordinates, numeric base zero (decimal, octal, or hexadecimal), zero padding, and so on. The output sequence can even include expressions that use the parameters incalculation, for example, to increment values. In many cases, Uniface adapts the way it operates based on which parameters are included. The exact parameters passed and how Uniface reacts are described with each mnemonic. For example, if the %p parameter is not included in the output sequence for the buzz mnemonic, Uniface assumes that the device cannot buzz several times with one command; the buzz command is then activated p times. Table 1. Parameters in the output sequence Parameters Meaning %h %v Horizontal and vertical starting coordinates. %m Repetition ( m times) of character. Useful for white space. %m %n Horizontal width and vertical depth. %x %y Horizontal and vertical ending coordinates. %p %q General parameters, often used as a kind of counter. %w %d Character width and depth, that is, resolution. Formatting the Output Sequence All of these parameters can be preceded by a number which determines how Uniface formats the data, that is, which base (decimal, octal, or hexadecimal), and whether the number should be padded with zeros to a fixed length. The syntax is shown in the table, where a question mark (?) is a single digit 1 through 9: Table 2. Data Formatting Syntax Parameters Meaning %0p or %p Decimal value with variable number of digits (that is, no padding). %?p Decimal value padded with leading zeros to ? digits. %10p Octal value with variable number of digits. %1?p Octal value padded with leading zeros to ? digits. %20p Hexadecimal value with variable number of digits. %2?p Hexadecimal value padded with leading zeros to ? digits. %30p Binary value, bytes ordered low to high, variable number of bytes. %3?p Binary value, bytes ordered low to high. %40p Binary value, bytes ordered high to low, variable number of bytes. %4?p Binary value, bytes ordered high to low. For example, if Uniface needs to pass the value 17 as a parameter, the table shows the literal values that are generated with the corresponding codes: Table 3. Examples: Data Formatting Parameters Parameter Meaning Value generated %0p Decimal. 17 %3p Decimal, padded to three digits. 017 %14p Octal, padded to four digits. 0021 %20p Hexadecimal. 11 Expressions in an Output Sequence Uniface also supports expressions within an output sequence. An expression must be enclosed in parentheses. The indicator for base and padding of the final result goes between the percent sign (%) and the opening bracket (() of the expression. Values within the expression are always decimal; formatting occurs at the last step. All operators supported by the ProcScript language are available here, including brackets (()). The expressions can use integer constants and all parameters appropriate for the particular mnemonic. Parameters within the expression are not preceded by a percent sign (%). Spaces are allowed within the expressions to increase readability. If a part of the expression contains a comparison operator (for example, =, <, >, and so on) that section expression is evaluated as a Boolean expression. For example, %(2+2<(2+1)) is evaluated as 3. A few examples are given in the table: Table 4. Examples: Expressions in Parameter Declarations Parameters Meaning %(p+1) Increase ‘p’ by one. %24(8 * (y + w * 16)) Use ‘y’ and ‘w’ in a calculation. %(p%8) Use modulus to compute a value between 0 and 7, inclusive. Was this topic helpful? Like Dislike"}